Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "crnac" (which translates to "black person" or "negro" in English):

1. *Crnac* je igrao košarku sa mojim prijateljima sinoć. (A *black person* played basketball with my friends last night.)
2. Često čujem kako ljudi koriste reč *crnac* na uvredljiv način. (I often hear people use the word *black person* in an offensive way.)
3. Kada sam bio u Americi, imao sam mnogo prijatelja *crnaca*. (When I was in America, I had many *black* friends.)
4. Kolega mi je *crnac* i ima sjajno smisao za humor. (My colleague is *black* and has a great sense of humor.)
5. Nažalost, mnogi ljudi i dalje imaju predrasude prema *crncima*. (Unfortunately, many people still have prejudices against *black people*.)
6. Neki kažu da bi trebalo izbegavati korišćenje reči *crnac* i koristiti termin "afroamerički" umesto toga. (Some say that the use of the word *black person* should be avoided and instead use the term "African American".)
7. Da li si primetio da u ovom restoranu nema ni jednog *crnca*? (Have you noticed that there are no *black people* in this restaurant?)
8. Volim da slušam muziku koju izvode *crnci*. (I love listening to music performed by *black people*.)

Note: Please keep in mind that some people may find the use of the word "crnac" offensive, and it is always important to use language that is respectful and inclusive of all individuals.